1️⃣ Install Vercel CLI
npm install -g vercel

Used to deploy your project and run locally.

2️⃣ Initialize your project folder
mkdir shopify-coverage-proxy
cd shopify-coverage-proxy
npm init -y

Creates package.json.

3️⃣ Install dependencies
npm install node-fetch

Needed for calling the Dolphin API in validate.js.

4️⃣ Create API folder and files
mkdir api
touch api/validate.js

We put the Node.js function (validate.js) here.

5️⃣ Add your validate.js code
const fetch = require('node-fetch');

module.exports = async (req, res) => {
  if (req.method !== 'POST') return res.status(405).json({ error: 'Method not allowed' });

  const { address } = req.body;
  if (!address || !address.trim()) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Address missing' });

  const username = 'client_hy4kcyqls6xp';
  const password = 'Zde02cfBnYsIwsgddlk6jiiYxMxO0Cw0';
  const authHeader = 'Basic ' + Buffer.from(`${username}:${password}`).toString('base64');

  try {
    const response = await fetch(
      'https://dolphin-telecoms-coverage-map-api.lionafricadigital.com/api/external/coverage/validate',
      {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Accept':'application/json', 'Content-Type':'application/json', 'Authorization': authHeader },
        body: JSON.stringify({ address, service_use: "Home" })
      }
    );

    const text = await response.text();
    try { return res.status(200).json(JSON.parse(text)); } 
    catch { return res.status(200).send(text); }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error("Vercel proxy error:", err);
    return res.status(500).json({ error: 'Could not validate coverage. Try again.' });
  }
};
6️⃣ Test locally
vercel dev

Runs the API at http://localhost:3000/api/validate for local testing.

7️⃣ Deploy to Vercel
vercel


7️⃣ Deploy to Vercel production
vercel prod
